13/09/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Police on Friday (September 11th) arrested early eight people in the regions of Belgrade, Smederevo, Kraljevo and Vrnjacka Banja, suspected of large-scale embezzlements at the State Railway company.
The group, which is believed to have abused their power, allegedly stole about 746,000 euros through two of the company's subsidiaries, where they worked.
(Glas Javnosti - 12/09/09;
B92, Press, Vecernje Novosti, e-Novine, RTS - 11/09/09)
